title: Was a Ray Malabar Sefet car observed during the 19th lockdown?
subtitle: The shelter orders in the middle of the corona virus epidemic may have given wildlife - and our imagination - a small extra room for wandering.
author: Dan Evon
vclaim: For the first time since the 1990s, Seifet Malabar, who was at high risk during a COVID-19 closure operation in India, was seen.
